<div id="review_2796533030" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2796533030" />
    <a title="Annabelle Heath" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/95690092-annabelle-heath"><img alt="Annabelle Heath" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1555687038p2/95690092.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2796533030?book_show_action=true">Apr 23, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Annabelle Heath" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Annabelle Heath" href="/user/show/95690092-annabelle-heath">Annabelle Heath</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/95690092-annabelle-heath?shelf=read-in-2013">read-in-2013</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2796533030" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18095648966292804696">Peter Octavian is a vampire PI. Which always sets alarm bells ringing in my head, but Golden&apos;s vampire world is original, well constructed and as full of blood and sex as a vampire world ought to be. Peter is looking for a missing girl. Through his investigations, he comes to realise that she isn&apos;t the only one who&apos;s disappeared or died under mysterious circumstances. A secret sect of the church are trying to bring about the end of all vampires and they&apos;re planning to finish the job.<br/><br/>An entertain</span>
  <span id="freeText18095648966292804696" style="display:none">Peter Octavian is a vampire PI. Which always sets alarm bells ringing in my head, but Golden's vampire world is original, well constructed and as full of blood and sex as a vampire world ought to be. Peter is looking for a missing girl. Through his investigations, he comes to realise that she isn't the only one who's disappeared or died under mysterious circumstances. A secret sect of the church are trying to bring about the end of all vampires and they're planning to finish the job.<br /><br />An entertaining read with great world building. I'll definitely be reading the sequel.</span>
  <a data-text-id="18095648966292804696" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
