<div id="review_3324003370" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3324003370" />
    <a title="Random" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5876789-random"><img alt="Random" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1319569701p2/5876789.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3324003370?book_show_action=true">May 19, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Random" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Random" href="/user/show/5876789-random">Random</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/32184895-of-saints-and-shadows">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3324003370" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4115868210350320532">Great story, really good world-building, hampered by some poor writing. There’s some good writing in here, too. I feel like I’m reading early age YA (which this not), when how the lead characters’s feelings are half of every scene. Especially when they are the same feeling described, over and over (Meghan). SHOW don’t tell. I’m not a slimmer but I learned to skim the “how feeling” paragraphs of this work.<br/><br/>IThe story is good enough to keep me going, I’ll read at least one more.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


